<br>
Also I feel that many organised religions try to give people moral rules to live their lifes by, things like contraception is wrong etc etc. I feel that I'm capable of deciding my own morals, and values, and dont need a religion telling me how I should live. <br>
<br>
To me theres one simple rule to live your life by, or maybe it is two, Strive to do no deliberate harm to other living beings and treat people kindly and with compassion. Other than that do what we wish, if it harms no one. I think these views are similar to buddhist views, maybe Loknar can tell me?<br>
<br>
I dont mind whether people are religous or not, I'm willing to respect their believes and feelings, so long as they dont start trying to convert me. I dont mind talking about people's religions, but dont want to be pressurised to accept religous views.<br>
<br>
Western religions dont really appeal to me or interest me, but I am very interested in spirituality. The eastern religions, things like Buddhism in it's various forms, appeal to me quite alot, and I like to read about them. <br>
<br>
I meditate, and stuff, and though my main aim in doing that is inner peace, I also hope that it will make me a more spiritual person, I dont have any preconceptions of what I want to learn from meditation I just think it will be an interesting journey. And hopefully I'll be calmer and better for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><CENTER>===Silva===</CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.silvas-world.co.uk">Silva's World</A></CENTER>
